<div id="review_3000306419" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3000306419" />
    <a title="Mobeme53 Branson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3380946-mobeme53-branson"><img alt="Mobeme53 Branson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1386284695p2/3380946.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3000306419?book_show_action=true">Oct 09, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mobeme53 Branson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mobeme53 Branson" href="/user/show/3380946-mobeme53-branson">Mobeme53 Branson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11007316-love-in-a-dry-season">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3000306419" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7479558143736924307"><strong>Good but overrated</strong><br/><br/>My opinion is that Mr Foote, in this novel, is a bit too clever for his own good. Some of the analogies he draws are stretching it too far for my liking. He is a excellent writer for the major part and excellent at drawing characters. I&apos;m not saying it should be required, but I didn&apos;t like any of the people in the book. They were all lacking in either moral values or of, for lack of a better word, gumption. I understand the use of the pejorative word Nigger in context; however,</span>
  <span id="freeText7479558143736924307" style="display:none"><strong>Good but overrated</strong><br /><br />My opinion is that Mr Foote, in this novel, is a bit too clever for his own good. Some of the analogies he draws are stretching it too far for my liking. He is a excellent writer for the major part and excellent at drawing characters. I'm not saying it should be required, but I didn't like any of the people in the book. They were all lacking in either moral values or of, for lack of a better word, gumption. I understand the use of the pejorative word Nigger in context; however, he uses it in sentences that clearly are not necessary. An example would be when he describes a paint color as "Nigger Pink." What does that even mean. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="7479558143736924307" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


