<div id="review_75596604" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/75596604" />
    <a title="Elizabeth K." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2467151-elizabeth-k"><img alt="Elizabeth K." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1303134380p2/2467151.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/75596604?book_show_action=true">Oct 24, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elizabeth K." class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elizabeth K." href="/user/show/2467151-elizabeth-k">Elizabeth K.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2467151-elizabeth-k?shelf=2007-new-reads">2007-new-reads</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer75596604" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1626972025322617726">Oh, this was lovely. Southern drama, infidelity, revenge and family strife, what more do you need in a book? The plot is fairly straightforward -- a stranger arrives in the Mississippi Delta (not the delta of the Mississippi River), from the North, obviously, because where else would upheaval come from? and tangles in turn with a sheltered old maid and a wealthy, restless young married.<br/><br/>Grade: A<br/>Recommended: Must-read for those captivated by Southern Gothic. It&apos;s also a bit on the mild side of the</span>
  <span id="freeText1626972025322617726" style="display:none">Oh, this was lovely. Southern drama, infidelity, revenge and family strife, what more do you need in a book? The plot is fairly straightforward -- a stranger arrives in the Mississippi Delta (not the delta of the Mississippi River), from the North, obviously, because where else would upheaval come from? and tangles in turn with a sheltered old maid and a wealthy, restless young married.<br /><br />Grade: A<br />Recommended: Must-read for those captivated by Southern Gothic. It's also a bit on the mild side of the genre, it's not the way out grotesque of Flannery O'Connor, nor heavily convoluted like Faulkner.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1626972025322617726" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


