<span id="freeTextContainer6296368142181546472"><strong>Mayhem among moonlight and magnolias I 1930-40s Mississippi</strong><br/><br/>Chosen for a book club. None of the members knew of his work beyond the Civil War trilogy so interesting to see a different side.<br/>3 of 10 members were so turned off by the book they gave up before getting 25% through it, as one member said there was no character he liked or wanted to follow.<br/>Recommend to those who don&apos;t need purity or probity in their protagonists. If you liked Vanity Fair you&apos;ll likely enjoy this book.</span>
